tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,Wait time,
review:
I recently had the privilege of consulting with Dr. Abhishek Modi regarding a gum grafting procedure, and I am incredibly impressed with his expertise and patient-centric approach.

First and foremost, Dr. Modi is an exceptionally friendly and approachable dentist. From the moment I stepped into his office, I felt welcomed and at ease. He greeted me with a warm smile and took the time to understand my concerns thoroughly.

What truly set Dr. Modi apart was his dedication to providing detailed explanations during the consultation. He patiently walked me through the entire gum grafting procedure, ensuring that I had a clear understanding of what it entailed. His ability to convey complex information in a simple and understandable manner was truly commendable and greatly appreciated.

Even though my visit with Dr. Modi was for a consultation only, I left feeling informed, confident, and reassured about the potential treatment. His professionalism and commitment to patient care are evident in every aspect of his practice.

I wholeheartedly recommend Dr. Abhishek Modi to anyone seeking dental care or consultation, especially for gum grafting. His friendly demeanor, thorough explanations, and genuine concern for his patients make him a standout healthcare professional. Thank you, Dr. Modi, for your outstanding service and dedication to your patients' well-being.

tags: Doctor friendliness,Explanation of the health issue,Treatment satisfaction,Value for money,
review: Dr Abhishek was very helpful and explained the entire problem very nicely. He ensured that the procedure is as painless as possible. review: I visited the clinic for a consultation on teeth alignment issue. On inquiring before the appointment, I was told what the consultation fee would be. During the appointment, the doctors performed a dental scan of my teeth. However, I was not told that the scan would be chargeable and this made my final consultation fee to be almost 5x the amount I was initially informed about. My issue is with the failure to inform and the let patient know about if any additional scan/checkup that is required to be done would come with an extra charge.
